ditionally skip loading if the platform can't handle it. I need to be cautious about potential rules against skipping or short-circuiting native images. There's a thought about adding test resources for native-image metadata to help with runtime initialization, but maybe that's not feasible. I should check existing tests with custom ClassLoaders, as native might allow loading known classes without defining new ones. I wonder if the native image supports class loading with the same application loader too.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating class loading**\\n\\nI’m thinking about class loading, particularly how some tests might use a custom ClassLoader. The use of `java.net.URLClassLoader` in the JVM could be beneficial if classes aren’t initialized. I might want to check the TCK native config to see if all tests run properly. It’s probably not a big deal, but I need to consider using Surefire include. Ultimately, I should inspect the user-code filter before deciding on creating a new public API test and committing.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_6NmsIj5znasQLoeKK7COkwPP|fc_058dea4977c0b3380169f01a0bc0f08196a5d5c7607c5e28c9", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/com.thoughtworks.xstream/xstream/1.4.20/user-code-filter.json", "limit": 200}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 9382, "output": 1183, "cacheRead": 29696, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 40261, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777342965463, "responseId": "resp_058dea4977c0b3380169f019f5e9888196bdf5daf6099a9b5d"}}
